    "body": "> Does it make sense to return this for negative confirmations?\r\n\r\nIn this case per `CachedTxIsTrusted()` the `trusted` field will always return false, which, along with the `walletconflicts` field returning txids of conflicting txs, seems good to return to the user. So the existing behavior appears to be fine but the RPC helps are incorrect. Though I could imagine one could also argue for always returning the `trusted` field or only returning it if `confirmations` equals 0.",
